From d0612cbc8c7507566f2d967f541754698cfe33f3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Max Furman <taygoth@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 00:22:25 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 8/9] arm64: dts: qcom: add Xiaomi Mi 8 (dipper)

Add a device tree for the Xiaomi Mi 8 (codename "dipper"),
a SDM845-based smartphone.

Working with this DT and the matching userspace overlay:
display (Samsung EA8074), touchscreen (FTM5), rear main camera
(IMX363), audio (WCD9340 codec, TAS2557 speaker amp, q6voice path),
Wi-Fi (ath10k WCN3990), Bluetooth (WCN3990 UART6), modem data,
SMS and voice calls, USB peripheral, UFS storage, GPU (A630),
fuel gauge, charger and volume keys.

USB-C: enables PMI8998 Type-C through the multi-chip TCPM driver
with USB-PD restricted to a single 5V PDO (safe profile). sink-vdos
identity advertised so PD partners ACK Discover_Identity without
issuing SOFT_RESET. dwc3 in OTG mode with usb-role-switch wired to
the PMI8998 TCPM connector subnode.

SLPI is intentionally left disabled until a mainline-side sensor
consumer exists.

The DT describes one tested physical variant ("new MP v2.1",
p0 camera pinout, Semco IMX363); other Mi 8 variants may need
DT changes.

Signed-off-by: Max Furman <taygoth@gmail.com>
